//sitebuildercontent/sitebuilderpictures/druidpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Running of the Nekkid Trolls..Or Ogres</span><hr size=1> I was just thinking of having a guild event called &quot;Running of the Trolls&quot; or &quot;Ogre Run&quot;<br>
(Yeah I know its been done but I love seeing the carnage)<br>
For those of you that dont know its a newbie run (Level one) To a set point chosen by the guild (Like the bank in North Freeport) Closest to the destination (Aka the corpse) Wins the set amount. This event would have a time limit.<br>
<br>
We could also have at the same time a battle royal by class,This would be level based.<br>
A player would pay an entry fee and they would fight in the PVP arena (Lets say warrior for example)<br>
They would gather in the arena and wait for the appointed signal (Probally a shout from the designated Referee) And begin Melee. The last warrior left alive would win a percentage of the entry fees.<br>
<br>
Also we could have a scavenger hunt (No no drop items for obvious reasons) and have an entry fee for that also.<br>
The first person back with All the items is proclaimed the winner and recieves a percentage of all the entry fees.<br>
<br>
To keep it interesting we could post a temporary website with all the items and shout the URL on where to find the list so the people will have to camp to get at the list. (Heheheh)I think 8 items would be adequate. Also this event would have a time limit (a guild member would get all the items and write down how long it took them)<br>
<br>
I think this is a great way to increase guild coffers and mayhaps increase guild membership....Remember people love being in a guild that does things together.  <br>
If anyone else can think of events or has positive  or negative  feedback on this subject please leave some comments.<br>
<br>
Thank you for your time in perusing through my thoughts<br>
(Although sometimes twisted as they may be :P)<br>
